<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h1>Tutorial 4. Pinning and Basting the Seams.</h1>
<h3>Topstitching the Seams and Sewing Boning Tunnels.</h3>
<p><strong>I pin the lining to the leather face of the corset.</strong> I carefully bring pins through the seams piercing the face and the lining. I try my best not to damage the leather. Pins should go right in and out the groove of the seam.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I have pinned all three seams on the first half of the corset (the central front piece is still detached).</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image010.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>Next I baste the seams with contrasting thread folded in half.</strong> It is easier to remove contrasting thread from the seam after sewing boning tunnels. I highly recommend that you use a thimble too. These basting stitches are not supposed to be too loose so I keep pulling the thread to prevent the seam from going undone during topstitching. I sew right through the groove of the seam. Remember to make a back stitch every couple of centimeters to preserve the degree of thread tension.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image013.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image015.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image017.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The first half of the corset is ready. I baste the seams on the second half exactly the same way.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image019.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image021.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Now I need to topstitch the seams and sew boning tunnels.</strong></p>
<p>Let me remind you that I use 8mm flexible spiral bones and 1cm flat bones. I will sew 1.2cm tunnels for the spirals and 1.4cm tunnels for the flats. The major lacing area is at the back of the corset so I will place two flat bones there. It is enough to place one flat bone at the front of the corset to join it with the central front piece.</p>
<p><strong>I topstitch both sides of each seam 1-2mm from the edge.</strong> I use a Teflon presser foot and set the stitch length to 4mm.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image023.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image025.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image027.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>With thick thread like Synton, it is best not to interrupt the row of stitches but pass onto the next half of the corset, make a bar tack, and only then cut the thread.</strong> The beginning of the row will look neater this way and you won't have to tie all those knots.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image029.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image031.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image033.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image035.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image037.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image039.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image041.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image043.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image045.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image047.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image049.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image051.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image053.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image055.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I have topstitched the seams on both halves of the corset.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image057.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image059.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>It's time to sew tunnels for flexible spiral bones.</strong> I step 1.2cm from either side of topstitching.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image061.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image063.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image065.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image067.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image069.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image071.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image073.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image075.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image077.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image079.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image081.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image083.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image085.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>Tunnels for flexible spiral bones are ready.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image087.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I fold the front and the back edge of each half of the corset and press them with a warm iron to make them neat and pretty. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image089.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Now I can sew tunnels for flat bones.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image091.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>There will be one flat bone at the front of either half of the corset,</strong> so I simply make one row of stitches 1.4cm from the edge. Later I will install grommets for lacing the central front panel to the corset.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image093.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image095.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image097.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I form lacing bars at the back of the corset as per usual.</strong> I make a row of stitches to form a tunnel for the first flat bone, then I make another row of stitches 1cm from it to mark the grommet area, and then another row of stitches to form a tunnel for the second flat bone.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image099.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image101.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image103.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image105.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image107.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image109.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image111.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/leather%20corset/gothic%20corset/transcripts/Tutorial%204_files/image113.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>All I need to do now is remove the contrasting thread, install grommets, and finish the top edge and the hem of the corset.</p>
<p>But before doing all that, let us decorate the removable central front panels of the corset.</p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
